Peru Stocks: Alturas, Atacocha, Buenaventura, Maple, Relapasa

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-03-28T21:46:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/peru-stocks-alturas-atacocha-buenaventura-maple-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peruvian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 5.2 percent to 21,095.67, the
biggest drop since June 2009. The MSCI All  Peru  Capped Index
declined 5 percent to 2,847.24.  Mining stocks fell after a poll published by Lima-based
research Ipsos Apoyo showed opposition presidential candidate
Ollanta Humala leading less than two weeks before the April 10
elections. Humala said he’d renegotiate energy and mining
contracts with foreign companies if he wins next month’s vote.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, plunged 10 percent to 18 cents. Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc
producer, dropped 7.7 percent to 1.2 soles Soc. Minera El Brocal
SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer, dropped 7.4
percent to 49.99 soles. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE),
the country’s biggest precious-metals miner, fell 3.1 percent to
$42.45. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s biggest
silver producer, fell 5.1 percent to 3.75 soles, the most since
June 2009.  Fuel refiners dropped after crude futures in New York fell.
Crude for May delivery fell 1.4 to $103.98 a barrel on the  New
York Mercantile Exchange .  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, declined 6.6 percent to 1.83 soles.  Maple Energy
Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with operations
in Peru, dropped 7.9 percent to 93 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
